flowRoot.flowPara: Use the page switcher above or use one of the following:
/* FIXME: we need a fallback icon in case the icon is not found */
/* TODO: merge existing item properties with new values. */
Hidden project panel (focused frame is indicated by the text color in the header):
Shows all open "pages" (files, terminals, documentation). The list of open pages is global rather than per frame.
Only shown if a document outline is available. Could also potentially incorporate a list of issues in the document.
Back/forward buttons navigate between pages. Ideally history would be per-frame.
Save isn't shown in the menu, but it could be. Frame section is only shown when there's more than one frame.
List of terminal options is highly tentative.
Save all has been removed from the hamburger menu. It could potentially be reintroduced.
+ button is shown for the current directory. Display options which are currently in the context menu should be moved to the preferences.
Back, forward and close buttons are insensitive. So is the frame popover if there's only one frame.
